"Make sure that flight mode is turned off and check your data or Wi-Fi connection."

"Nokia respects your privacy. Upon device activation your unique device and network information is sent to Nokia Corporation. This information enables us to better meet demand in your country, provide software updates, support Nokia customer care, and activate Nokia services. It will not be used to identify you personally or for direct marketing."

"We will not sell collected information for any purpose. We may only share it with other Nokia companies or authorised third parties who process it on our behalf or when there is a legal obligation to do so."

"Information may be transferred across international borders and outside Europe in compliance with applicable laws. We use appropriate information security measures to protect the information."

"You have a right to access or rectify your personal data. To exercise your rights, contact us through www.nokia.com or directly at Nokia Corporation c/o Privacy, FIN-Keilalahdentie 4, 02150 Espoo, Finland."

"Additional privacy or other notices may be provided when you use different features of your device. Your use of Nokia services and applications in your device is governed by the Nokia Terms of Use and Privacy Policy. You can read them any time by visiting www.nokia.com/privacy."
"Your opinion is very valuable to Nokia, so please tell us what you think of your new phone."\n\n"If you would like to take part in this survey later, you can find it from Settings."
